name: <collections::btree::set::BTreeSet<T> as core::default::Default>::default

collections::btree::set::BTreeSet::<T>::.doc:
Makes a new, empty `BTreeSet`.

 Does not allocate anything on its own.

 # Examples

 ```
 # #![allow(unused_mut)]
 use std::collections::BTreeSet;

 let mut set: BTreeSet<i32> = BTreeSet::new();
 ```
